children.text: There are areas where the roof battens have been installed with adjacent splices on top chords, or with more than 1 in 3 battens spliced on any top chord.
The relevant Australian Standard, AS 4440 Installation of Nail-Plated Timber Roof Trusses, clause 4.2 Roof Battens, and the truss manufacturer’s installation instructions state that

‘The stability of any roof system is reliant on the tile or sheeting battens. Battens to be arranged so that on any truss top chord, not more than 1 in 3 battens are spliced and no two splices are adjacent’ .

These roof battens should be reconstructed in accordance with the manufacturer’s installation instructions and Australian Standard AS 4440. Alternatively, the builder should provide the owner with documentation from the manufacturer to confirm that the current installation is acceptable.
